The two men that escaped from police custody this morning.&nbsp;Photo supplied.Date: 01 December 2016 By: Isabel VenterViewed: 981Police are on the look-out for two suspects that escaped from the Mara Police cells this morning (1 December).According to police information the two men were involved in an attempted robbery on a farm in the Mara area. During their arrests police seized fire-arms.The two suspects must be considered dangerous, and should not be approached. If spotted, it must be reported to the police immediately by phoning the Makhado Police Station at Tel 015&nbsp;519 4300 or 079 889 6222. Alternatively, the Crime Stop number can be called at 0860 01 0111 or the 24-hour crime line at 32211.The two escaped wearing the same clothes that they were photographed in.Isabel joined the Zoutpansberger and Limpopo Mirror in 2009 as a reporter. Her beat is mainly crime and court reporting. At present, she is studying for her BA Degree through the University of South Africa.Email: isabel@zoutnet.co.zaMore photos... 